{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":853,"text":"What do you think would happen"},{"time":3248,"text":"if you invited an individual\nwho had been living on the street"},{"time":6177,"text":"for many years,"},{"time":7747,"text":"had mental health issues"},{"time":10457,"text":"and was an alcoholic"},{"time":12168,"text":"to move directly from the street"},{"time":14277,"text":"into housing?"},{"time":16233,"text":"We had heard this was being done\nin New York City,"},{"time":19174,"text":"and it was called the Housing First model."},{"time":21199,"text":"We wondered if it would work in Utah."}]},{"cues":[{"time":24038,"text":"So to make that determination,\nwe decided to create a pilot,"},{"time":27727,"text":"and Keta was one of the 17\nchronically homeless individuals"},{"time":33002,"text":"we included in this pilot."},{"time":34906,"text":"She had been on the street\nfor 20-plus years,"},{"time":38368,"text":"had mental health issues"},{"time":40357,"text":"and was a severe alcoholic."},{"time":43193,"text":"The first night in her apartment,"},{"time":45303,"text":"she put her belongings on the bed"},{"time":47820,"text":"and slept on the floor."},{"time":49605,"text":"The next three nights,\nshe slept out by the dumpster"},{"time":52320,"text":"near the apartment building."},{"time":54815,"text":"With the aid of her case manager,"},{"time":56730,"text":"she moved back into her apartment"},{"time":58867,"text":"but continued to sleep on the floor\nfor several nights."},{"time":62688,"text":"It took over two weeks for her\nto develop enough trust and confidence"},{"time":67940,"text":"that this apartment was hers"},{"time":70392,"text":"and would not be taken away from her"},{"time":72482,"text":"before she would start\nsleeping in the bed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":75580,"text":"Homelessness is a continuing\nchallenge for many cities"},{"time":78362,"text":"throughout our country."},{"time":80174,"text":"Our homeless population falls\ninto three major categories:"},{"time":83804,"text":"those that are temporarily homeless,"},{"time":85971,"text":"about 75 percent;"},{"time":87722,"text":"those that are episodically homeless,"},{"time":89627,"text":"about 10 percent;"},{"time":91209,"text":"and those that are chronically homeless,"},{"time":93279,"text":"about 15 percent."},{"time":95653,"text":"Chronic homelessness is defined\nas an unaccompanied adult"},{"time":99458,"text":"who has been continuously\nhomeless for a year or more"},{"time":102684,"text":"or more than four times\nhomeless in three years"},{"time":105598,"text":"that totals 365 days."},{"time":108325,"text":"This small 15 percent\nof the homeless population"},{"time":111920,"text":"can consume 50 to 60 percent\nof the homeless resources"},{"time":116196,"text":"available in a community."},{"time":118140,"text":"In addition, they can cost the community"},{"time":121735,"text":"20,000 to 45,000 dollars a year per person"},{"time":125905,"text":"in emergency services costs,"},{"time":128554,"text":"such as EMT runs,"},{"time":130495,"text":"emergency room visits,\nas many of you will be aware,"},{"time":133658,"text":"addictions, interactions with the police,"},{"time":136695,"text":"jail time."},{"time":138551,"text":"Simply put, this small\npopulation costs a lot."}]},{"cues":[{"time":144147,"text":"Based on this reality, the US government\nbegan an initiative in 2003"},{"time":148639,"text":"inviting states and cities and counties"},{"time":151799,"text":"to develop a plan to end\nchronic homelessness"},{"time":154846,"text":"in a 10-year period."},{"time":156798,"text":"The state of Utah accepted\nthis invitation,"},{"time":158988,"text":"and I was asked to lead this effort."},{"time":162485,"text":"In 2005, we approved a 10-year plan,"},{"time":165658,"text":"and 10 years later, in 2015,"},{"time":168819,"text":"we reported a reduction\nin our chronic homeless population"},{"time":171909,"text":"of 91 percent statewide."}]},{"cues":[{"time":175587,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":180962,"text":"That's amazing."},{"time":183437,"text":"When I began this process,\nand we began this process,"},{"time":187471,"text":"I realized that I had a limited\nunderstanding of homelessness"},{"time":192136,"text":"and the factors that impacted it,"},{"time":194400,"text":"and that I needed a fairly major change\nin my belief, in my thinking,"},{"time":198837,"text":"because I had been raised\nwith the theory of rugged individualism"},{"time":202677,"text":"and \"pull yourself up by the bootstraps.\""},{"time":204791,"text":"That philosophy came from being raised\non our family's cattle ranch"},{"time":208001,"text":"in a small town\nin the western desert of Utah."},{"time":211113,"text":"On the ranch, you learned\nthat nothing takes priority"},{"time":214684,"text":"over caring for the cattle,"},{"time":216710,"text":"something always needs fixing"},{"time":218904,"text":"and most importantly,"},{"time":220752,"text":"hard work makes the world right."},{"time":223805,"text":"It was through that lens\nthat I would see homeless people."},{"time":226642,"text":"When I was a teenager, our family\nwould go into Salt Lake City,"},{"time":229685,"text":"and I would see these homeless people --\n\"hobos\" we called them then --"},{"time":233169,"text":"sitting around on the street,"},{"time":234599,"text":"and I would think,"},{"time":235788,"text":"\"You lazy bums, get a job.\nPull yourself up by the bootstraps.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":241926,"text":"After high school, I left the ranch,"},{"time":244000,"text":"graduated from college,"},{"time":246116,"text":"went to work for Ford Motor Company\nfor several years,"},{"time":249691,"text":"then got a job at the Church\nof Jesus Christ of Latter Day Saints"},{"time":253015,"text":"and moved back to Salt Lake City."},{"time":255620,"text":"During that employment,\nI had the opportunity to be loaned out"},{"time":258633,"text":"to the state's largest homeless shelter"},{"time":260576,"text":"to assist them in developing and improving"},{"time":262666,"text":"their financial\nand management capabilities."}]},{"cues":[{"time":265610,"text":"While there, I became aware\nof a new approach"},{"time":269879,"text":"to dealing with homeless individuals"},{"time":272090,"text":"and drug addicts."},{"time":274486,"text":"It was called the harm reduction model,"},{"time":276996,"text":"and it consisted of passing out\nclean needles and condoms."},{"time":280633,"text":"And I thought, \"Now that\nis one stupid idea.\""},{"time":283365,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":284612,"text":"\"That's just going to encourage them\nto continue that behavior."},{"time":287631,"text":"Just tell them to stop.\""},{"time":291323,"text":"Several years later, I read\nsome of the early 10-year plans"},{"time":294341,"text":"to end chronic homelessness"},{"time":295740,"text":"promoted by the federal government."},{"time":297721,"text":"As I read through those plans,\nand I thought,"},{"time":301041,"text":"\"Pfft! This is unrealistic."},{"time":302720,"text":"You can't end homelessness."},{"time":304271,"text":"There's too many personal choices\nand factors beyond our control.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":309724,"text":"My perspective changed, however,"},{"time":312242,"text":"when I attended a conference in 2003,"},{"time":315213,"text":"where I learned the reason\nbehind the 10-year plan."},{"time":319626,"text":"First was this small population\nof the homeless group"},{"time":323799,"text":"that was 15 percent\nand were very expensive."},{"time":327216,"text":"That made sense"},{"time":328541,"text":"for a conservative state like Utah."}]},{"cues":[{"time":331663,"text":"The second insight was learning\nabout this Housing First,"},{"time":335064,"text":"or low-barrier housing."},{"time":336933,"text":"There had been an agency in New York City"},{"time":339086,"text":"that had been inviting\nmentally ill homeless individuals"},{"time":342296,"text":"to move directly\nfrom the street into housing."},{"time":346487,"text":"And they were also allowed to continue\nto use drugs and to drink,"},{"time":350736,"text":"just like we can in our homes."},{"time":352401,"text":"They were, in addition, offered\nservices -- not required to use them --"},{"time":357149,"text":"by on-site case managers"},{"time":358576,"text":"to assist them to adjust\nto their new living arrangements"},{"time":361481,"text":"and to stabilize their lives."},{"time":363644,"text":"They were using the harm reduction model."},{"time":367322,"text":"And despite my initial low expectations\nabout hearing about this model,"},{"time":372355,"text":"they were having\nan astonishing success rate:"},{"time":374749,"text":"85 percent were still housed\nafter 12 months."}]},{"cues":[{"time":379380,"text":"The third insight"},{"time":381434,"text":"was the importance of developing\na trusting relationship."},{"time":385239,"text":"Because of the abuse\nthese individuals have had"},{"time":388447,"text":"throughout most of their lives,"},{"time":390455,"text":"they hardly trust anybody,"},{"time":394031,"text":"and the clean needles and condoms\nand low-barrier housing"},{"time":398138,"text":"was a means to begin to develop\na relationship of trust."},{"time":403270,"text":"Vital."}]},{"cues":[{"time":407472,"text":"So as I flew home from this conference,"},{"time":411048,"text":"sitting in the plane\nlooking out the window,"},{"time":414121,"text":"I realized that my understanding\nand perspective about homelessness"},{"time":417928,"text":"was shifting."},{"time":420070,"text":"And as I stared out that window,"},{"time":421965,"text":"this very strong feeling\nand thought came to me"},{"time":424828,"text":"that if there's any state in the union"},{"time":426801,"text":"that could end chronic homelessness,"},{"time":428810,"text":"it was the state of Utah,"},{"time":431155,"text":"because there's an underlying feeling"},{"time":433981,"text":"and desire and willingness\nto collaborate to serve our neighbors,"},{"time":438811,"text":"including those who are homeless."},{"time":443376,"text":"A new vision was becoming clear to me\nhow this could be done."}]},{"cues":[{"time":449214,"text":"Now, those of us that attended\nthe conference said,"},{"time":451688,"text":"\"Yeah, these models will work in Utah.\""},{"time":453613,"text":"But when we got back home,\nthere were many who said,"},{"time":456100,"text":"\"Nah, those aren't going to work.\nThey won't succeed here.\""},{"time":459256,"text":"But there was, however,\nan affordable housing organization"},{"time":462330,"text":"who was willing to build\nour first 100 units."},{"time":466280,"text":"But they had concerns about having\n100 chronically homeless people"},{"time":469787,"text":"in one location."},{"time":471594,"text":"To address that concern,\nwe decided to create a pilot"},{"time":476097,"text":"to test that idea while we built\nthe first 100 units."},{"time":479589,"text":"We would use existing units\nscattered throughout Salt Lake City."}]},{"cues":[{"time":484523,"text":"Then we debated:"},{"time":485968,"text":"Should we select fairly\nhigh-functioning homeless persons"},{"time":489784,"text":"or the most challenging\nones we could find?"},{"time":492693,"text":"And this is where my background\non the ranch came into play."},{"time":496753,"text":"Back then, my mother cooked our meals"},{"time":499250,"text":"and heated the water for our weekly bath"},{"time":502342,"text":"on a wood-burning and coal-burning stove."},{"time":505663,"text":"And after chopping wood\nfor that stove all those years,"},{"time":508770,"text":"I'd learned to chop\nthe big end of the log first,"},{"time":511175,"text":"when I had the most energy."},{"time":513907,"text":"We decided to use the \"big end\nof the log first\" approach"},{"time":517680,"text":"and selected 17 of the most challenging,"},{"time":521051,"text":"difficult, chronically homeless\npeople we could find,"},{"time":524903,"text":"because we knew we would learn\nthe most from them."},{"time":529438,"text":"Twenty-two months later,"},{"time":532287,"text":"all 17 were still housed,"},{"time":537148,"text":"including Keta,"},{"time":538932,"text":"who today, 11 years later,"},{"time":541615,"text":"is sleeping in her own bed"},{"time":543848,"text":"and is sober."}]},{"cues":[{"time":546450,"text":"At the end of this pilot,\none of the young case managers said,"},{"time":549516,"text":"\"We used to debate\nup at our university classes"},{"time":551836,"text":"which theory of case management\nwas the most effective."},{"time":555275,"text":"Now our theory of case management is:"},{"time":557673,"text":"anything necessary to keep them housed.\""},{"time":561868,"text":"We became believers,"},{"time":563713,"text":"and built hundreds of units\nover those next 10 years,"},{"time":567221,"text":"leading to the reduction of our statewide\nchronic homeless population"},{"time":571319,"text":"of 91 percent."}]},{"cues":[{"time":573445,"text":"Now, who are homeless people?"},{"time":576116,"text":"Many people just want them\nto go away, to disappear,"},{"time":579191,"text":"not disrupt our lives."},{"time":581427,"text":"Through this 10-year, 11-year process,\nI gained many insights"},{"time":584692,"text":"of why people become homeless."},{"time":587247,"text":"One of those insights\ncame to me a few years ago"},{"time":589659,"text":"when I was visiting\nwith our medical outreach team."},{"time":592294,"text":"These are our frontline workers"},{"time":593842,"text":"that go out and visit\nthe street homeless and the prostitutes"},{"time":596724,"text":"to check on their medical health."},{"time":600588,"text":"One of the team members mentioned"},{"time":602184,"text":"that eight of the prostitutes\nhad given birth to 31 children"},{"time":606132,"text":"that had become wards of the state."},{"time":608592,"text":"They also shared that some of the pimps\nwere their husbands,"},{"time":611548,"text":"and worse yet,"},{"time":612766,"text":"their parents."},{"time":616151,"text":"These prostitutes,"},{"time":617964,"text":"in their late teens, 20s, early 30s,"},{"time":621114,"text":"were expected to earn\nenough money a day to support"},{"time":624653,"text":"a hundred-dollar-a-day heroin addiction,"},{"time":626858,"text":"their living expenses"},{"time":628239,"text":"and their pimp."},{"time":630615,"text":"And with unprotected sex,\nthey were paid more,"},{"time":633498,"text":"and predictably,\nthis would lead to a pregnancy."},{"time":638219,"text":"Children born under these circumstances\nmany times end up becoming homeless."},{"time":643763,"text":"And it's not helpful to look at\nthose born under those circumstances,"},{"time":648452,"text":"or a parent that makes their child\na drug addict at age seven,"},{"time":652042,"text":"or a generation of babies\nborn through drug addiction,"},{"time":655990,"text":"and not feel some despair."},{"time":658184,"text":"For me, I believe\nevery person is of value,"},{"time":663379,"text":"no matter who you are."},{"time":666827,"text":"And it's not helpful to look\nat somebody with this start in life"},{"time":670905,"text":"and blame them for where they are."}]},{"cues":[{"time":675843,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":681666,"text":"No one grows up saying,\n\"My goal in life is to become homeless.\""},{"time":687798,"text":"And that's the beauty of the harm\nreduction and Housing First model."},{"time":692877,"text":"It recognizes the complexities\nof the different factors"},{"time":696636,"text":"that can shape a human life."},{"time":698570,"text":"These models meet people where they are,"},{"time":702740,"text":"not where we are"},{"time":704807,"text":"or where we think they should be."}]},{"cues":[{"time":708891,"text":"The pilot we did with our 17\ntaught us many lessons."},{"time":714953,"text":"When people have been living\non the street for many years,"},{"time":717777,"text":"moving back into housing"},{"time":720218,"text":"requires lots of things to learn."},{"time":723570,"text":"And Donald"},{"time":726417,"text":"taught us some\nof these transition lessons."},{"time":729068,"text":"His case manager asked him\nwhy he had not turned up the heat"},{"time":732027,"text":"in his cold apartment."},{"time":733986,"text":"Donald said, \"How do you do that?\""},{"time":736412,"text":"He was shown how to use a thermostat."},{"time":739694,"text":"The case manager also observed"},{"time":741636,"text":"that he was heating the beans\nin the can on the stove,"},{"time":745075,"text":"like he had done over\nthe campfires for many years."},{"time":748902,"text":"He was shown how to use pots and pans."},{"time":751850,"text":"We also learned that he had a sister\nthat he had not seen in 25 years,"},{"time":755437,"text":"who thought he was dead."},{"time":757643,"text":"She was happy to learn otherwise,"},{"time":759534,"text":"and they were soon reconnected."},{"time":761833,"text":"Hundreds of people like Keta\nand Donald are now housed"},{"time":766095,"text":"and reconnecting with their families."},{"time":768980,"text":"Also, many of our\ncommunities are incurring"},{"time":771260,"text":"fewer emergency services costs."}]},{"cues":[{"time":774919,"text":"I have learned over and over again"},{"time":778395,"text":"that when you listen to somebody's story\nwith an open heart,"},{"time":782466,"text":"walk in their shoes with them,"},{"time":784707,"text":"you can't help but love and care for them"},{"time":788721,"text":"and want to serve them."},{"time":792595,"text":"This is why I'm committed"},{"time":795253,"text":"to continuing to bring hope and support\nto our homeless citizens,"},{"time":800751,"text":"who I consider to be\nmy brothers and sisters."}]},{"cues":[{"time":804735,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":805915,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}